          presentations: [{
            text: '<div>\n\t<div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<strong>现在完成时态中的副词</strong><br />\n\t\t\t&nbsp;</div>\n\t</div>\n\t<div>\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width: 100%;" width="700">\n\t\t\t\t<tbody>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td colspan="3">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t用副词 **yet**, **already**, **never**和**ever**在现在完成时中表示从过去直到现在的一段时间。<br />\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td colspan="3">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<strong>&#39;Yet</strong>&#39;<br />\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td colspan="3">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t用副词**yet** 表示某事尚未发生，或询问某事是否已经发生。该副词常放在句尾。<br />\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style="width: 5%;">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/11/04/23/v/110423/GE_5.1.4.3.1_1_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td style="width: 40%;">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<em>I haven&#39;t printed my boarding pass <strong>yet</strong>.</em></td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t我还没有打印登机牌。</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/11/04/24/v/110424/GE_5.1.4.3.1_2_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<em>They haven&#39;t packed their bags <strong>yet</strong>.</em></td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t他们还没有收拾行李。</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/11/04/25/v/110425/GE_5.1.4.3.1_3_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<em>Has she left for the airport <strong>yet</strong>?</em></td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t她已经出发去机场了吗？</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t</tbody>\n\t\t\t</table>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>',
            layoutType: 'Table'
          }, {
            text: '<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width: 100%;" width="700">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan="3">\n\t\t\t\t<strong>&#39;Already&#39;</strong><br />\n\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan="3">\n\t\t\t\t使用副词**already** 来表达某事已经发生，或询问某事是否已经发生。该副词常直接放在主要动词之前。<br />\n\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style="width: 5%;">\n\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/11/04/26/v/110426/GE_5.1.4.3.1_4_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t<td style="width: 40%;">\n\t\t\t\t<em>You can&#39;t come? But I&#39;ve <strong>already</strong> booked the tickets!</em></td>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t你来不了吗？可我机票都定好了！</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/11/04/27/v/110427/GE_5.1.4.3.1_5_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t<em>Carly has <strong>already</strong> been to Paris, but I haven&#39;t.</em></td>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\tCarly 已经去过巴黎，我还没去过。</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/11/04/28/v/110428/GE_5.1.4.3.1_6_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t<em>Has John <strong>already</strong> been to the Louvre?</em></td>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\tJohn 已经去过卢浮宫了吗？</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>',
            layoutType: 'Table'
          }, {
            text: "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width: 100%;\" width=\"700\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"3\">\n\t\t\t\t<strong>'Never' 和'ever' \r\n \r\n</strong><br />\n\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"3\">\n\t\t\t\t用副词**ever**询问是否有事情发生，或谈论某人的经历。作为否定的回应，用**never**，这类副词常常放在主要动词前面。<br />\n\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"width: 5%;\">\n\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/11/04/29/v/110429/GE_5.1.4.3.1_7_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"width: 40%;\">\n\t\t\t\tA: <em>Have you <strong>ever</strong> lived in another country? </em><br />\n\t\t\t\tB: <em>No, I&#39;ve <strong>never</strong> lived in another country.</em></td>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t你在其他国家生活过吗？<br />\n\t\t\t\t不，我从未居住在另一个国家。</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"3\">\n\t\t\t\t<br />\n\t\t\t\t语言提示：学习者的一个普遍的错误是在肯定句中使用副词**ever** ，注意在例子中做出正确反应。<br />\n\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/11/04/22/v/110422/GE_5.1.4.3.1_8_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\tA: <em>Have you <strong>ever</strong> been to Paris?</em><br />\n\t\t\t\tB: <em>Yes, I have been to Paris.</em></td>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t您去过巴黎吗？<br />\n\t\t\t\t是的，我去过巴黎。</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>",
            layoutType: 'Table'
          }]
